title: Independent Candidate wins PK-97 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Muhammad Khurshid has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-97, Karak-I by securing 51,994 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent Candidate Mian Nisar Gul who bagged 21,387 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 43.58 per cent.
